comments.content:
"List of the steps involved in PKA activation:
1. Cytosolic cAMP increases.
2. Two cAMP molecules bind to each PKA regulatory subunit.
3. The regulatory subunits move out of the active sites of the catalytic subunits and the R2C2 complex dissconnects.
4. The free catalytic subunits interact with proteins to phosphorylate Ser or Thr residues." [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protein_kinase_A#Activation]
"There are ten known isoforms of adenylyl cyclases in mammals" [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adenylyl_cyclase]
Phospholipidase C; "class of membrane-associated enzymes that cleave phospholipids just before the phosphate group" [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phospholipase_C]
